        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 25 at 5:16PM EDT by NWS Northern Indiana</headline>
        <description>At 516 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Fort Shawnee, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lima, Fort Shawnee, Harrod, Beaverdam, Westminster, Yoder, Hume,
Slabtown, Rockport, Kemp, and Rousculp.

This includes Interstate 75 between mile markers 119 and 138.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
